if a file is open we can not delete that file
and in java as well if we are reading a file and didn't close that file we cannot delete that file
checked and unchecked exceptions
checked exceptions:they are special type of exceptions that you cannot handle them without try catch
you can not handle them with if elseif condition you must have a try catch block
they are more dangerous they are exceptions which are beyond the control of a programmer
unchecked exceptions: are light weight you can ignore them they can be handled by if else if conditions
Exceptions in java:
    Exception in java is an unwanted behaviour that disrupts the normal flow of execution.